“I wanted this three-act performance to be our way of keeping a record of these extraordinary times where the situation demands more of us than a simple runway show. I wanted a film directed by an artist with a feel for the crossover of genres and disciplines. Not a film about fashion, nor about dance, but a film about us all and all the ways we can and must continue to reinvent ourselves.”
Nadège Vanhée-Cybulski, Artistic Director of Women’s ready-to-wear

node.text:
Can you silk me?​

Let me introduce myself. I am a silk cashmere scarf knotted with nonchalance and decontracted elegance. I believe that effortlessness is the new cool. I am inspired by big city metro lines, my pocket square has the letters H E R M E S hidden somewhere. The stations have been transformed into the links of the Chaine d'Ancre, a subtle reference to the iconic motif of Hermès. Voilà!​
👀​

Silk Masquerade, pepper faces on parade.

 Ok, ok, it's not pepper, it's salt! Salt artist @bashirsultani brings condiments to the table as he takes on American illustrator Daniel Clowes to recreate the belle of the ball.
